                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2091b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-09T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 9, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>372. 1. Repeat to Peck Department’s 367, October 7, 8 p.m.<note n="13"
                        xml:id="d154fn13">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>2. Inform Peck that the Secretary of State had a long conversation with the
                    Chinese Chargé on October 8. The Secretary explained our attitude and policy and
                    urged necessity for self-control on part of both the Japanese and the Chinese
                    nations. He has repeatedly urged same on Japanese Ambassador.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
